Wim Pretorius, News24Nelson Mandela. (File, AFP) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; Former South African president and world famous icon Nelson Mandela&rsquo;s entire inheritance&nbsp;has been&nbsp;allocated to his beneficiaries as was requested in his will, former Deputy Chief Justice Dikgang Moseneke announced on Friday. The list of 40 beneficiaries announced at the Nelson Mandela Foundation in Houghton, north of Johannesburg, included his long-time driver, three members of his staff at his private home, as well as all the high schools and universities he attended while growing up.His late son Makgatho Mandela&rsquo;s children: Mbuso Mandela &ndash; R3 122 220 Andilo Mandela &ndash; R 3 122 220 Ndaba Mandela &ndash; R 3 122 220His daughter Makaziwe Mandela&rsquo;s children: Dumani Mandela &ndash; R100 000 Tukwini Mandela &ndash; R100 000 Adjao Amuah &ndash; R100 000 Kweko Amuah &ndash; R100 000His daughter Zenani Mandela-Dlamini&rsquo;s children: Zinhle Mandela &ndash; R100 000 Zaziwe Mandela &ndash; R100 000 Zamaswazi Mandela &ndash; R100 000His daughter Zindzi Mandela's children: Bambatha Mandela &ndash; R100 000 Zondwa Mandela &ndash; R100 000 Zwelabo Mandela &ndash; R100 000 Zoleka Mandela &ndash; R100 000His daughter Zamaswazi&rsquo;s child: Zozuko Mandela &ndash; R100 000 Mandela also allocated a large sum of money to the children of third wife Gra&ccedil;a Machel's children, who were born to the late president of Mozambique, Samora Machel. Josina Machel and Malengande Machel will each receive R3m. He also left R100 000 each to Samora Machel&rsquo;s six children born from a previous marriage. The six are Joselina, Samora Junior, Manthyane, Atwane, Turila, and Olivia Machel.Fort Hare University and the University of Witwatersrand will each receive R100 000, while the Qunu Secondary School and Orlando West High School have also been awarded R100 00